that's a local promoter

230
00:09:43.374 --> 00:09:45.960
<i>here in San Antonio.</i>

231
00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:49.089
We go down there.
and Jose Lothario was there.

232
00:09:49.172 --> 00:09:53.593
‐ From San Antonio. Texas.
superstar Jose Lothario.

233
00:09:53.676 --> 00:09:55.261
‐ <i>I understood
he was a legitimate name.</i>

234
00:09:55.345 --> 00:09:57.764
<i>The gentleman stated
"Well. he has to be trained.</i>

235
00:09:57.847 --> 00:10:00.600
<i>"Jose could do the training
if you wanted.</i>

236
00:10:00.683 --> 00:10:03.311
It's gonna cost $3.000."

237
00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:05.647
‐ <i>I thought
about facing him</i>

238
00:10:05.730 --> 00:10:08.983
<i>when he was 35
or 40 years old.</i>

239
00:10:09.067 --> 00:10:10.485
and having him say

240
00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:14.489
"Dad. if you'd have
just given me the chance.

241
00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:17.492
I could have been
a professional wrestler."

242
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:19.577
And I couldn't face
that thought.

243
00:10:19.702 --> 00:10:27.502
And so I said.
"What the hell."

244
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:31.965
<i>[soft music]</i>

245
00:10:32.048 --> 00:10:33.800
‐ <i>You know.
I wake up every day</i>

246
00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:37.804
<i>never forgetting
what I did for a living.</i>

247
00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:40.682
<i>I sort of developed a habit
getting up in the morning.</i>

248
00:10:40.765 --> 00:10:42.725
<i>stretching
and then the heat pad.</i>

249
00:10:42.851 --> 00:10:45.061
Over the years. you just
come up with a system

250
00:10:45.186 --> 00:10:48.857
that your body responds
well to.

251
00:10:48.982 --> 00:10:52.152
<i>I do some form of training
every day. you know.</i>

252
00:10:52.235 --> 00:10:55.363
<i>to be comfortable
for the rest of the day.</i>

253
00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:58.491
I plan on getting. you know.
new knees. knee replacements

254
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.201
and shoulder replacements.

255
00:11:00.285 --> 00:11:03.872
<i>Those things are gonna add
to my quality of life.</i>

256
00:11:03.997 --> 00:11:05.540
<i>It's not like
I got into this stuff thinking</i>

257
00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:10.295
<i>I want to be independently
wealthy and be 100% healthy.</i>

258
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:11.504
<i>That doesn't happen.</i>

259
00:11:11.629 --> 00:11:13.173
So I don't know.
I don't mind it.

260
00:11:13.298 --> 00:11:17.135
I don't think that's some big.
crazy sacrifice.

261
00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:20.263
<i>♪</i>

262
00:11:22.599 --> 00:11:25.143
<i>[upbeat music playing]</i>

263
00:11:25.268 --> 00:11:30.815
‐ <i>I first came
across Shawn Michaels in 1983.</i>

264
00:11:30.899 --> 00:11:32.358
Shawn was training
with a gentleman

265
00:11:32.483 --> 00:11:34.068
by the name of Jose Lothario.

266
00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:37.864
<i>Jose was a big star
in Houston. Texas.</i>

267
00:11:37.947 --> 00:11:39.908
<i>Dallas. San Antonio.</i>

268
00:11:40.033 --> 00:11:43.703
‐ <i>He was Hispanic.
so there was a Luchador style.</i>

269
00:11:43.828 --> 00:11:46.748
<i>It was the aerial side
of things.</i>

270
00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:49.042
<i>Thankfully.
in all of that process.</i>

271
00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:53.463
he saw that. "Oh. my goodness.
he's actually pretty good."

272
00:11:53.546 --> 00:11:55.965
<i>It was worth
the $3.000. period.</i>

273
00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:58.593
for him to get me
my first job in Louisiana.

274
00:11:58.676 --> 00:11:59.928
<i>and that could not
have happened</i>

275
00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:01.262
<i>without Jose Lothario.</i>

276
00:12:01.346 --> 00:12:05.725
‐ <i>The pride of Vero Beach.
Florida. Terry Taylor.</i>

277
00:12:05.850 --> 00:12:07.644
‐ <i>The first time
I met Shawn Michaels</i>

278
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:09.562
<i>working for Mid‐South.</i>

279
00:12:09.687 --> 00:12:12.148
there was this young.
innocent. cheerful.

280
00:12:12.232 --> 00:12:13.816
vibrant sort of

281
00:12:13.942 --> 00:12:15.944
<i>lost young man.</i>

282
00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:17.987
‐ <i>I was scared
of everything.</i>

283
00:12:18.071 --> 00:12:20.823
It was a lot of confusion.
a lot of unknown.

284
00:12:20.949 --> 00:12:23.826
How in God's name
is this supposed to go on?

285
00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:24.953
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

286
00:12:25.036 --> 00:12:26.329
<i>I came walking
through the back.</i>

287
00:12:26.412 --> 00:12:28.456
<i>and Terry Taylor was
standing there at the curtain.</i>

288
00:12:28.539 --> 00:12:30.083
‐ I said. "How long have you
been in the business?"

289
00:12:30.166 --> 00:12:31.709
And he goes.
"That was my first match."

290
00:12:31.834 --> 00:12:34.629
And I couldn't believe it.
because this isn't easy.

291
00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:36.005
‐ <i>Shawn Michaels.</i>

292
00:12:36.089 --> 00:12:38.967
A very young man.
and very inexperienced.

293
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:41.511
but he has a great deal
of natural athletic ability.

294
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:44.097
‐ <i>We drove
3.000 miles a week.</i>

295
00:12:44.180 --> 00:12:45.640
That means there's
a lot of time

296
00:12:45.682 --> 00:12:46.891
that you're in the car
doing this.

297
00:12:46.975 --> 00:12:48.184
<i>and he would ask questions.</i>

298
00:12:48.309 --> 00:12:50.645
‐ <i>A young man
who is quite handsome.</i>

299
00:12:50.728 --> 00:12:52.814
‐ <i>I was very well mannered.
I was quiet.</i>

300
00:12:52.939 --> 00:12:54.315
and I wanted to do
nothing but learn.

301
00:12:54.399 --> 00:12:56.943
‐ <i>Some young people
come in. "I know everything."</i>

302
00:12:57.026 --> 00:12:58.903
<i>Nothing like that with Shawn.</i>

303
00:12:59.028 --> 00:13:02.156
<i>Humble. passionate.
driven. hungry.</i>

304
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:03.825
[crowd cheers]

305
00:13:03.866 --> 00:13:06.703
‐ <i>At about six months.
the owner. Bill Watts.</i>

306
00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:10.748
<i>came to me and he got me
set up in Kansas City.</i>

307
00:13:10.873 --> 00:13:13.084
I was going to have
the opportunity to begin

308
00:13:13.167 --> 00:13:17.463
to grow as a wrestler.
as a performer.

309
00:13:17.588 --> 00:13:19.090
‐ <i>We're hearing
all this. like.</i>

310
00:13:19.173 --> 00:13:20.967
<i>this guy Shawn Michaels.
Shawn Michaels is coming in.</i>

311
00:13:21.009 --> 00:13:22.885
We're like.
"Damn. nobody has gotten

312
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:24.846
"any attention like this.

313
00:13:24.971 --> 00:13:26.431
What's wrong with us?"

314
00:13:26.514 --> 00:13:27.932
<i>We walked in the dressing room</i>

315
00:13:28.016 --> 00:13:30.059
<i>and this guy had
real short hair.</i>

316
00:13:30.184 --> 00:13:33.396
green tights pulled up
to under his chest.

317
00:13:33.479 --> 00:13:34.981
<i>Let me ask this nerd. like.</i>

318
00:13:35.064 --> 00:13:36.983
<i>"Hey. do you know
who Shawn Michaels is?"</i>

319
00:13:37.066 --> 00:13:39.652
And he leaned back he goes.
"I'm Shawn Michaels."

320
00:13:39.736 --> 00:13:41.446
[laughs]

321
00:13:41.529 --> 00:13:43.990
I was like. "Oh. damn.
we got some work to do."

322
00:13:44.073 --> 00:13:45.116
<i>They threw us
together because</i>

323
00:13:45.199 --> 00:13:46.367
<i>they needed
a match real quick.</i>

324
00:13:46.492 --> 00:13:50.788
We didn't have time to prepare
for it. but it clicked.

325
00:13:50.872 --> 00:13:52.332
‐ <i>Marty Jannetty.</i>

326
00:13:52.373 --> 00:13:54.959
‐ <i>Marty just carried himself
with such confidence.</i>

327
00:13:55.043 --> 00:13:57.962
<i>He was enjoying himself.
He was outgoing.</i>

328
00:13:58.046 --> 00:14:01.466
I was so sort of shy.
conservative.

329
00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:02.717
‐ <i>Shawn Michaels.</i>

330
00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:04.552
‐ <i>Shawn came
from a military family.</i>

331
00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:09.015
<i>Shawn was protected
from a lot of the evils</i>

332
00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:11.267
that lurk in the real world

333
00:14:11.351 --> 00:14:13.436
<i>and having some notoriety.
being on television.</i>

334
00:14:13.519 --> 00:14:16.439
<i>you've got women. you've got
alcohol. you've got drugs.</i>

335
00:14:16.522 --> 00:14:19.567
And it's all readily
available to you.

336
00:14:19.650 --> 00:14:21.152
‐ <i>Yeah.
he liked it right away.</i>

337
00:14:21.235 --> 00:14:23.905
<i>At first.
he wasn't old enough.</i>

338
00:14:23.988 --> 00:14:25.239
so he had to wait
in the parking lot.

339
00:14:25.365 --> 00:14:28.576
We'd bring girls down to him
and beer down to him.

340
00:14:28.701 --> 00:14:30.161
‐ <i>Marty Jannetty
one day said.</i>

341
00:14:30.244 --> 00:14:34.207
"I see something in you
that's just dying to get out."

342
00:14:34.332 --> 00:14:35.708
He said.
"You just need somebody

343
00:14:35.833 --> 00:14:37.126
"to bring it out of you.

344
00:14:37.210 --> 00:14:38.711
and I'm gonna bring it out."

345
00:14:38.836 --> 00:14:41.422
‐ <i>From the Showboat
Hotel and Casino</i>

346
00:14:41.506 --> 00:14:43.132
<i>in Las Vegas. Nevada.</i>

347
00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:46.928
<i>this is AWA Championship
Wrestling on ESPN.</i>

348
00:14:47.011 --> 00:14:48.805
‐ <i>So. I was 20 years old.</i>

349
00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:51.349
<i>TV tapings are in Las Vegas.</i>

350
00:14:51.474 --> 00:14:53.142
<i>At that time.
Marty and I. you know.</i>

351
00:14:53.226 --> 00:14:54.143
<i>I knew he was out there.</i>

352
00:14:54.227 --> 00:14:57.271
so we just started
looking around.

353
00:14:57.355 --> 00:14:58.481
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

354
00:14:58.523 --> 00:15:01.651
All of a sudden there he is.
he's down there playing.

355
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:03.069
And go down there.

356
00:15:03.194 --> 00:15:05.696
and I went and just do‐do‐do.
pulled it down.

357
00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:06.906
‐ <i>I'm sitting there with him.</i>

358
00:15:07.031 --> 00:15:08.157
<i>and all of the sudden
we hear this.</i>

359
00:15:08.282 --> 00:15:09.742
"Ding. ding. ding.
ding. ding. ding."

360
00:15:09.826 --> 00:15:14.288
Red lights go flashing around.
and Shawn hit triple 7s.

361
00:15:14.372 --> 00:15:17.208
Won 750 bucks
the first time.

362
00:15:17.333 --> 00:15:21.796
The irony of it now. like.
oh. this place was‐‐

363
00:15:21.879 --> 00:15:22.964
<i>Vegas and the nightlife
of Vegas</i>

364
00:15:23.089 --> 00:15:24.674
<i>and everything else
would be my down‐‐</i>

365
00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:25.967
[laughs]
Would be my downfall.

366
00:15:26.008 --> 00:15:27.802
It started later that night.

367
00:15:27.844 --> 00:15:30.680
<i>It's the first line of yayo.
you know.</i>

368
00:15:30.805 --> 00:15:33.224
[laughs]
The first line of blow.

369
00:15:33.349 --> 00:15:37.437
And it's. "Oh. my gosh. this
is the greatest thing ever."

370
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:40.648
<i>And it's just this
whole world opens up.</i>

371
00:15:40.731 --> 00:15:43.192
<i>I'd have never been able
to get that guy out of me.</i>

372
00:15:43.317 --> 00:15:46.320
<i>and Marty is the guy
that helped tap into that.</i>

373
00:15:46.404 --> 00:15:48.573
I don't even know
how much I knew was there.

374
00:15:48.698 --> 00:15:49.824
<i>♪</i>

375
00:15:49.866 --> 00:15:52.869
‐ <i>Me and Shawn partied
Monday night. Tuesday night.</i>

376
00:15:52.994 --> 00:15:54.662
Wednesday night.
Thursday night.

377
00:15:54.745 --> 00:15:56.164
Come Friday.
we were burned out.

378
00:15:56.205 --> 00:15:59.125
<i>Big Van Vader.
he comes to hang out with us.</i>

379
00:15:59.208 --> 00:16:01.461
<i>He looked at Curt Hennig
and he goes.</i>

380
00:16:01.544 --> 00:16:04.005
"I thought you said
these guys partied."

381
00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:06.716
And Curt said. "They don't
start until midnight."

382
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:08.134
‐ <i>The Midnight Rockers.</i>

383
00:16:08.259 --> 00:16:10.344
<i>What a sensational pair
they are.</i>

384
00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:13.973
‐ It was like magic.
The Judas Priest song come on.

385
00:16:14.056 --> 00:16:17.143
‐ <i>They love to party.</i>

386
00:16:17.185 --> 00:16:18.853
‐ <i>They've taken
the AWA by storm.</i>

387
00:16:18.936 --> 00:16:19.979
‐ <i>The move
happening faster</i>

388
00:16:20.104 --> 00:16:21.397
<i>than we can
even talk about it.</i>

389
00:16:21.522 --> 00:16:22.857
‐ <i>They've got to put
a bigger roof on the arenas</i>

390
00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:24.150
<i>to hold these two kids in it.</i>

391
00:16:24.275 --> 00:16:26.861
‐ <i>These two
are indeed sensational.</i>

392
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.154
<i>to say the least.</i>

393
00:16:28.237 --> 00:16:31.616
<i>‐ ♪ Living after midnight</i>

394
00:16:31.699 --> 00:16:33.993
<i>♪ Rocking 'til the dawn</i>

395
00:16:34.076 --> 00:16:35.703
[crowd cheering]

396
00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:39.207
‐ <i>Midnight Rockers had
a hell of a run in the AWA.</i>

397
00:16:39.332 --> 00:16:41.334
<i>They'd had TV on ESPN.</i>

398
00:16:41.375 --> 00:16:42.877
‐ The World
Tag Team Championship

399
00:16:43.002 --> 00:16:44.962
is Marty Jannetty
and Shawn Michaels' goal.

400
00:16:45.087 --> 00:16:46.172
‐ <i>They were smaller guys.</i>

401
00:16:46.297 --> 00:16:48.716
but they could work
with the giants

402
00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:50.551
and have a great match.

403
00:16:50.676 --> 00:16:52.136
[crowd cheering]

404
00:16:52.220 --> 00:16:53.679
‐ <i>The Tag Team
Championship of the World</i>

405
00:16:53.804 --> 00:16:56.891
<i>is what they are fighting for
here tonight.</i>

406
00:16:57.016 --> 00:16:59.018
<i>‐ I think he cracked
his head on the cement</i>

407
00:16:59.143 --> 00:17:00.937
<i>when he went out there.</i>

408
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:02.605
‐ <i>The blood match.
if you will.</i>

409
00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:06.150
<i>was the first time that a
national audience got exposed</i>

410
00:17:06.275 --> 00:17:08.903
to the talent
of the Midnight Rockers.

411
00:17:08.986 --> 00:17:11.322
‐ <i>This is absolute mayhem.</i>

412
00:17:11.405 --> 00:17:14.617
‐ The match itself
was very bloody. very gory.

413
00:17:14.700 --> 00:17:17.036
‐ <i>One of the
toughest. roughest matches</i>

414
00:17:17.161 --> 00:17:19.247
<i>that we have ever seen.</i>

415
00:17:19.372 --> 00:17:20.498
‐ <i>That was kind of like</i>

416
00:17:20.581 --> 00:17:22.333
<i>a defining moment
in their career.</i>

417
00:17:22.416 --> 00:17:25.419
that they were made
at that level.

418
00:17:26.212 --> 00:17:28.089
‐ <i>If we was on the road
300 days a year.</i>

419
00:17:28.172 --> 00:17:29.924
<i>we partied 290 of them.</i>

420
00:17:30.007 --> 00:17:31.217
[laughs]

421
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:32.927
<i>We used to do a lot of drugs.</i>

422
00:17:33.010 --> 00:17:34.637
There was a lot
of powder around.

423
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:37.181
‐ <i>You look at rock stars
and you look at rock bands.</i>

424
00:17:37.265 --> 00:17:41.394
There was a tendency to want
to go wild and destroy things.

425
00:17:41.519 --> 00:17:43.229
<i>It's fun when you're young.</i>

426
00:17:43.312 --> 00:17:45.106
<i>because you feel like a rebel.</i>

427
00:17:45.189 --> 00:17:47.191
<i>We've made it. man.
Look at this.</i>

428
00:17:47.316 --> 00:17:49.360
And throw a beer bottle
up against the wall.

429
00:17:49.443 --> 00:17:51.529
and it was. like.
oh. we'll pay for it later.

430
00:17:51.654 --> 00:17:53.239
‐ <i>We always did the job.</i>

431
00:17:53.322 --> 00:17:54.407
<i>but it was just partying
all night.</i>

432
00:17:54.532 --> 00:17:56.742
Destroy your room
at the Showboat

433
00:17:56.867 --> 00:17:59.996
and we got the entire. uh. AWA.

434
00:18:00.037 --> 00:18:02.999
the entire company
got kicked out of there.

435
00:18:03.124 --> 00:18:07.211
<i>It wasn't very long
that we had a reputation.</i>

436
00:18:07.336 --> 00:18:12.174
And once you get it. everybody
else knows you got it.

437
00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:15.136
<i>WWE was starting
to really separate itself.</i>

438
00:18:15.219 --> 00:18:16.137
If that's where
you wanted to go.

439
00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:18.139
that's where you
set your goals.

440
00:18:18.180 --> 00:18:22.810
<i>Finally. Marty got the call
to go into New York.</i>

441
00:18:22.893 --> 00:18:28.691
‐ <i>In 1987. the Rockers
started in Buffalo. New York.</i>

442
00:18:28.816 --> 00:18:32.737
Marty and Shawn looked
at this as their big break.

443
00:18:32.862 --> 00:18:35.031
<i>That night in the bar.</i>

444
00:18:35.156 --> 00:18:37.450
the other talent
looked at Shawn and Marty

445
00:18:37.533 --> 00:18:42.163
as these two young punks
with a chip on their shoulder.

446
00:18:42.246 --> 00:18:43.581
<i>They're gonna have to earn</i>

447
00:18:43.664 --> 00:18:46.626
<i>the respect
of the WWE locker room.</i>

448
00:18:46.709 --> 00:18:49.170
‐ <i>We were scared. man.
We were scared.</i>

449
00:18:49.295 --> 00:18:53.257
So that night. that's why
we kind of kept to ourselves.

450
00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:55.051
and Terry Garvin come up
and he said.

451
00:18:55.176 --> 00:18:56.135
"No. don't do that.

452
00:18:56.218 --> 00:18:58.679
Don't do that.
Y'all have to mingle."

453
00:18:58.804 --> 00:19:02.558
‐ <i>And then all of a sudden
Jimmy Jack Funk. he came over.</i>

454
00:19:02.642 --> 00:19:05.853
<i>He's hammering down these
drinks and he's like. "Hey!</i>

