00:39:41.462 --> 00:39:43.715
<i>Getting beat up by nine guys
in Syracuse.</i>

944
00:39:43.798 --> 00:39:45.133
to me. there's not
a whole lot of shame in.

945
00:39:45.258 --> 00:39:48.428
You know. that kind of stuff
just sort of happens to me.

946
00:39:48.511 --> 00:39:49.721
I've got two choices‐‐

947
00:39:49.804 --> 00:39:52.432
sit home and cry.
or to come out and be a pain.

948
00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:55.643
And I got news for you.
folks. I'm all cried out.

949
00:39:55.768 --> 00:39:56.853
‐ This moment of existence

950
00:39:56.978 --> 00:39:59.272
was the 20 minutes
in the ring every night.

951
00:39:59.355 --> 00:40:01.024
<i>He wouldn't be messed up.</i>

952
00:40:01.107 --> 00:40:02.692
<i>He'd go in there
and he'd kill it every night.</i>

953
00:40:02.775 --> 00:40:05.069
and then the second
he was done‐‐

954
00:40:05.194 --> 00:40:06.863
[clicks tongue]

955
00:40:06.946 --> 00:40:09.490
"I'm in pain.
and I took some stuff.

956
00:40:09.574 --> 00:40:11.451
<i>"so I wouldn't be
in pain this morning.</i>

957
00:40:11.534 --> 00:40:12.744
<i>but I'm messed up."</i>

958
00:40:12.827 --> 00:40:14.662
Why would you hang out
with this misery 24/7?

959
00:40:14.704 --> 00:40:16.748
No. it's not.
It's again like your brother.

960
00:40:16.873 --> 00:40:18.750
It's like a family member.

961
00:40:18.875 --> 00:40:20.793
Shawn owes his life
to Triple H.

962
00:40:20.877 --> 00:40:24.047
Paul Leveque.
owes his life to him.

963
00:40:24.172 --> 00:40:25.465
<i>‐ Shawn Michaels knows</i>

964
00:40:25.590 --> 00:40:28.426
<i>that the greatest match
of his life</i>

965
00:40:28.509 --> 00:40:31.304
<i>must come this Sunday night.</i>

966
00:40:31.429 --> 00:40:33.806
By the time
you get to the mid‐90s.

967
00:40:33.932 --> 00:40:36.184
<i>Bret Hart
has become a crowd favorite.</i>

968
00:40:36.309 --> 00:40:40.813
<i>Bret is a very soft‐spoken.
quiet. Canadian gentleman.</i>

969
00:40:40.939 --> 00:40:44.776
<i>Shawn is an outspoken.
loud. brash American.</i>

970
00:40:44.859 --> 00:40:48.947
Only one person can
be the absolute alpha dog.

971
00:40:49.030 --> 00:40:52.617
<i>The Iron Man match.
the boyhood dream realized.</i>

972
00:40:52.700 --> 00:40:57.372
<i>it added another layer to the
Shawn Michaels character.</i>

973
00:40:57.497 --> 00:40:58.498
‐ <i>The Iron Man match.</i>

974
00:40:58.623 --> 00:41:00.333
it's the opportunity
where I get to.

975
00:41:00.458 --> 00:41:02.919
you know. get
my first world championship.

976
00:41:03.002 --> 00:41:05.797
‐ <i>There's only one
Heartbreak Kid!</i>

977
00:41:05.838 --> 00:41:10.218
<i>Unbelievable. what a ride!</i>

978
00:41:10.343 --> 00:41:12.011
‐ <i>An hour‐long match.</i>

979
00:41:12.095 --> 00:41:14.806
it's gonna be a long night at
the office. in wrestling terms.

980
00:41:14.931 --> 00:41:19.394
‐ <i>For the WWE Championship!</i>

981
00:41:19.519 --> 00:41:21.479
‐ We start to have our issues.

982
00:41:21.604 --> 00:41:24.649
You know. I was never
big on the Kliq idea.

983
00:41:24.732 --> 00:41:27.110
<i>It was a testy match
in a lot of ways.</i>

984
00:41:27.193 --> 00:41:29.278
‐ <i>Hart's in big trouble.</i>

985
00:41:29.362 --> 00:41:31.406
[cheers and applause]

986
00:41:31.531 --> 00:41:33.199
‐ <i>There was a famous part</i>

987
00:41:33.324 --> 00:41:34.659
where I jump off
the second rope.

988
00:41:34.784 --> 00:41:36.285
[groans]

989
00:41:36.369 --> 00:41:38.663
<i>He comes up and kicks me
in the face</i>

990
00:41:38.705 --> 00:41:39.872
<i>as hard as he could.</i>

991
00:41:39.998 --> 00:41:41.165
I mean. he almost
knocked me out.

992
00:41:41.290 --> 00:41:42.500
<i>‐ Oh. my goodness!</i>

993
00:41:42.583 --> 00:41:44.293
We stiff each other a lot
of times in that match.

994
00:41:44.419 --> 00:41:47.213
[cheering and chatter]

995
00:41:47.338 --> 00:41:50.299
‐ One. two. out!

996
00:41:50.425 --> 00:41:52.969
[bell dings]

997
00:41:53.094 --> 00:41:57.432
‐ <i>The boyhood dream
has come true!</i>

998
00:41:57.515 --> 00:41:59.058
‐ <i>The boyhood dream has
come true.</i>

999
00:41:59.183 --> 00:42:02.645
because that was Shawn's
boyhood dream. it was.

1000
00:42:02.770 --> 00:42:04.856
And that's exactly
what happened.

1001
00:42:04.939 --> 00:42:07.608
‐ <i>It was a very
big moment for my career.</i>

1002
00:42:07.692 --> 00:42:09.736
It's like. oh. it's the first
World Championship

1003
00:42:09.819 --> 00:42:11.988
and you go like. "Hmm.
I pictured it being different."

1004
00:42:12.071 --> 00:42:14.824
<i>I wasn't at a good place
and all that kinda stuff.</i>

1005
00:42:14.949 --> 00:42:18.077
<i>Just a lot of responsibility
that goes with that.</i>

1006
00:42:18.202 --> 00:42:20.246
Now every guy in that locker
room. their well‐being.

1007
00:42:20.371 --> 00:42:24.333
their life. you know.
their livelihood and all that

1008
00:42:24.417 --> 00:42:26.502
depends on the job
that you do.

1009
00:42:26.627 --> 00:42:29.672
<i>You know. it all
falls on your shoulders.</i>

1010
00:42:29.756 --> 00:42:31.299
The whole thing
was uncomfortable.

1011
00:42:33.384 --> 00:42:37.889
‐ <i>As we got into 1996.
Ted Turner. who owned WCW.</i>

1012
00:42:37.972 --> 00:42:41.642
<i>our competitors.
was being very aggressive</i>

1013
00:42:41.684 --> 00:42:45.480
in his quest for new talent.

1014
00:42:45.605 --> 00:42:47.732
<i>Scott Hall and Kevin Nash.</i>

1015
00:42:47.857 --> 00:42:52.612
they were going to leave
and go to Ted Turner's WCW.

1016
00:42:52.695 --> 00:42:54.822
<i>The last matches being</i>

1017
00:42:54.947 --> 00:42:58.618
<i>in New York
in Madison Square Garden.</i>

1018
00:42:58.701 --> 00:43:01.370
‐ <i>On my 19th. 1996.</i>

1019
00:43:01.454 --> 00:43:04.123
one of the greatest days
of wrestling.

1020
00:43:04.207 --> 00:43:05.833
and my life as well.

1021
00:43:05.958 --> 00:43:08.544
<i>Me and my friend went
to a house show</i>

1022
00:43:08.669 --> 00:43:09.962
<i>which was not televised.</i>

1023
00:43:10.088 --> 00:43:11.881
<i>we would sneak in
a camera past security</i>

1024
00:43:11.964 --> 00:43:14.509
<i>and we would film the shows.</i>

1025
00:43:14.592 --> 00:43:18.387
Shawn was my hero
and was my idol growing up.

1026
00:43:18.471 --> 00:43:19.931
[audience cheering]

1027
00:43:20.014 --> 00:43:21.557
<i>The ending shows
Shawn Michaels</i>

1028
00:43:21.682 --> 00:43:23.267
<i>giving Diesel a super kick.</i>

1029
00:43:23.351 --> 00:43:25.645
Match is over.

1030
00:43:25.770 --> 00:43:28.231
<i>And then all of a sudden
Razor Ramon comes out.</i>

1031
00:43:28.356 --> 00:43:29.816
<i>I'm like. "Oh. cool."</i>

1032
00:43:29.899 --> 00:43:32.485
They start hugging and I'm
screaming like a little girl.

1033
00:43:32.568 --> 00:43:34.070
<i>Oh. my God!</i>

1034
00:43:34.195 --> 00:43:35.363
<i>Who's this?</i>

1035
00:43:35.446 --> 00:43:37.073
<i>And it turns out to be
Hunter Hurst Helmsley.</i>

1036
00:43:37.156 --> 00:43:40.243
They all start hugging and. you
know. obviously saying goodbye.

1037
00:43:40.368 --> 00:43:43.329
<i>It was insane.
That night was magical.</i>

1038
00:43:43.371 --> 00:43:45.665
<i>Yeah!</i>

1039
00:43:45.748 --> 00:43:47.166
<i>The business was
well protected</i>

1040
00:43:47.291 --> 00:43:50.670
<i>up until then. and our cameras
still kept going.</i>

1041
00:43:50.753 --> 00:43:52.672
<i>The only camera
that was there.</i>

1042
00:43:52.755 --> 00:43:55.633
If we were not involved
in taping the curtain call.

1043
00:43:55.716 --> 00:43:59.387
it would not be talked
about as much today.

1044
00:43:59.512 --> 00:44:01.139
‐ <i>Place is going insane.</i>

1045
00:44:01.222 --> 00:44:03.558
Everybody knows everything
on the inside of the business.

1046
00:44:03.683 --> 00:44:05.017
There's no secrets.

1047
00:44:05.143 --> 00:44:06.644
<i>‐ People in the business
didn't like it.</i>

1048
00:44:06.727 --> 00:44:09.230
They thought it was
the worst thing that happened.

1049
00:44:09.355 --> 00:44:11.566
Here's this bad guy.
who we have no idea

1050
00:44:11.691 --> 00:44:13.985
is friends with all
these other guys.

1051
00:44:14.026 --> 00:44:16.362
‐ <i>It's breaking
the fourth wall</i>

1052
00:44:16.487 --> 00:44:17.864
<i>and just telling people.</i>

1053
00:44:17.947 --> 00:44:19.323
<i>"Everything we just did
is bull [bleep]. "</i>

1054
00:44:19.407 --> 00:44:22.827
Shawn Michaels is now hugging
and kissing the guy

1055
00:44:22.910 --> 00:44:25.997
that he's just spent 20 minutes
beating the hell out of.

1056
00:44:26.038 --> 00:44:27.540
We entertained you.
but now it's all over.

1057
00:44:27.623 --> 00:44:31.210
we're really good buddies.
Taboo in the wrestling business.

1058
00:44:31.335 --> 00:44:34.714
‐ <i>The tape
was leaked out to a writer.</i>

1059
00:44:34.839 --> 00:44:36.924
The tape blows up on its own.

1060
00:44:37.008 --> 00:44:38.843
‐ <i>I had no idea
that was gonna happen.</i>

1061
00:44:38.926 --> 00:44:41.846
It was something
that's never been done before.

1062
00:44:41.929 --> 00:44:46.601
I'm watching this and going.
"What the hell is going on?"

1063
00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:49.103
The Kliq was an insult
to our business.

1064
00:44:49.187 --> 00:44:51.272
If they had done that
in the '70s. early '80s.

1065
00:44:51.355 --> 00:44:53.608
they'd all four of them get
the [bleep] beat out of 'em.

1066
00:44:53.691 --> 00:44:57.862
They wrestle each other and
they all kiss and say goodbye.

1067
00:44:57.945 --> 00:44:59.780
‐ Somebody's gotta
go down for it.

1068
00:44:59.864 --> 00:45:02.992
<i>Kev's gone. Scott's gone.
Shawn's the champ.</i>

1069
00:45:03.075 --> 00:45:08.497
Stuff rolls downhill and.
yeah. it all rolled on me.

1070
00:45:08.581 --> 00:45:10.166
‐ <i>Triple H is the one</i>

1071
00:45:10.249 --> 00:45:13.336
<i>that probably paid
the heaviest price</i>

1072
00:45:13.461 --> 00:45:15.296
<i>as far as his career</i>

1073
00:45:15.379 --> 00:45:18.424
<i>kind of hitting
a roadblock at that point.</i>

1074
00:45:18.507 --> 00:45:20.134
Shawn didn't really
pay a price.

1075
00:45:20.218 --> 00:45:22.637
‐ <i>I was inherently
selfish regardless.</i>

1076
00:45:22.762 --> 00:45:27.475
so I'm sure I didn't feel
the compassion for him.

1077
00:45:27.558 --> 00:45:32.188
as maybe I should have.

1078
00:45:32.313 --> 00:45:34.690
‐ <i>There was a bit
of a shutdown on Shawn.</i>

1079
00:45:34.815 --> 00:45:37.652
<i>Business is‐‐it's okay.
but it's not great.</i>

1080
00:45:37.735 --> 00:45:38.945
<i>You know.
there's a lot of banter</i>

1081
00:45:39.028 --> 00:45:41.447
about Shawn's not
working as champion.

1082
00:45:41.530 --> 00:45:43.324
He's not drawing.

1083
00:45:43.407 --> 00:45:45.534
<i>He's collapsing
under the pressure.</i>

1084
00:45:45.618 --> 00:45:47.495
<i>I can see him
falling apart.</i>

1085
00:45:47.620 --> 00:45:51.165
Kevin and Scott are gone.
and I'm all he's got now.

1086
00:45:51.249 --> 00:45:52.416
<i>He's a mess.</i>

1087
00:45:52.541 --> 00:45:55.753
‐ <i>I felt a lot of pressure
and I didn't handle it well.</i>

1088
00:45:55.836 --> 00:45:57.672
For me. it was all about

1089
00:45:57.755 --> 00:45:59.590
running and escaping.
and honestly.

1090
00:45:59.674 --> 00:46:01.092
you know. there was running

1091
00:46:01.175 --> 00:46:03.135
and escaping from the dude
I'd become.

1092
00:46:03.261 --> 00:46:05.054
Better than having
to face that.

1093
00:46:05.137 --> 00:46:08.349
I might just take a few
of these and knock myself out.

1094
00:46:08.432 --> 00:46:10.810
Won't have to pay attention
to it till tomorrow.

1095
00:46:10.893 --> 00:46:12.520
‐ <i>He'd be pilled up.
passed out.</i>

1096
00:46:12.645 --> 00:46:16.232
put Shawn on a luggage cart
and roll him up to his room.

1097
00:46:16.315 --> 00:46:18.859
<i>and get him undressed.
take the dip out of his mouth.</i>

1098
00:46:18.985 --> 00:46:20.361
<i>and put him on his side.
put a pillow behind him</i>

1099
00:46:20.486 --> 00:46:22.446
<i>so he wouldn't roll over and
choke to death in his sleep.</i>

1100
00:46:22.530 --> 00:46:25.324
And set an alarm and get up
every two. three hours

1101
00:46:25.408 --> 00:46:26.575
to go check on him.

1102
00:46:26.659 --> 00:46:28.202
<i>And that was every night.</i>

1103
00:46:28.286 --> 00:46:32.206
Well. you know. every night?
Sad existence.

1104
00:46:36.627 --> 00:46:38.671
<i>[cheers and applause]</i>

1105
00:46:38.796 --> 00:46:40.965
‐ <i>What everybody
has to understand</i>

1106
00:46:41.007 --> 00:46:43.301
<i>about Shawn Michaels
is this‐‐</i>

1107
00:46:43.342 --> 00:46:44.635
If I wanna come out here

1108
00:46:44.760 --> 00:46:48.639
and look like a blithering
idiot on live TV.

1109
00:46:48.681 --> 00:46:50.850
believe me. I'm gonna do it.

1110
00:46:50.933 --> 00:46:54.228
Why?
Because I can.

1111
00:46:54.353 --> 00:46:56.772
‐ <i>He had a drug problem
for a while.</i>

1112
00:46:56.856 --> 00:46:58.316
<i>a serious one.</i>

1113
00:46:58.357 --> 00:47:02.611
<i>and he kind of fell
in the hole even deeper.</i>

1114
00:47:02.695 --> 00:47:06.157
But it wasn't until
he became champion

1115
00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:08.659
that I felt that Shawn. uh.

1116
00:47:08.784 --> 00:47:12.747
started to question himself.

1117
00:47:12.872 --> 00:47:14.999
‐ <i>I called his dad.
the colonel.</i>

1118
00:47:15.082 --> 00:47:16.917
<i>and said.
"I'd like to visit."</i>

1119
00:47:17.001 --> 00:47:18.794
So I flew down to meet him

1120
00:47:18.919 --> 00:47:21.297
and I'm saying. "You're probably
not aware of this.

1121
00:47:21.339 --> 00:47:24.592
Shawn really
has a drug problem."

1122
00:47:24.675 --> 00:47:26.052
The colonel got angry.

1123
00:47:26.177 --> 00:47:29.472
He just didn't want to hear it.

1124
00:47:29.597 --> 00:47:31.932
‐ I don't know that anybody
knew how to address it.

1125
00:47:32.016 --> 00:47:34.101
<i>Even things like rehab.
my parents.</i>

1126
00:47:34.185 --> 00:47:35.311
you know. God love 'em.

1127
00:47:35.394 --> 00:47:37.897
I don't that they knew
what it was that you did.

1128
00:47:37.980 --> 00:47:39.231
<i>except just to be worried.</i>

1129
00:47:39.357 --> 00:47:42.443
<i>Not long after that
I tweaked my knee.</i>

1130
00:47:42.526 --> 00:47:44.653
[cheers and applause]

1131
00:47:44.779 --> 00:47:46.322
<i>I went to this dude
in San Antonio</i>

1132
00:47:46.405 --> 00:47:48.824
<i>who doesn't know anything
about wrestling.</i>

1133
00:47:48.866 --> 00:47:50.326
and obviously sees
I've torn my ACL

1134
00:47:50.368 --> 00:47:52.244
and he's like.
"Dude. you're done."

1135
00:47:52.370 --> 00:47:56.499
You know. he said. "You're not
wrestling with a torn ACL."

1136
00:47:56.582 --> 00:48:00.044
<i>I know that over
the last several months.</i>

1137
00:48:00.169 --> 00:48:01.962
I've lost a lot of things.

1138
00:48:02.046 --> 00:48:03.464
and one of them
has been my smile.

1139
00:48:03.547 --> 00:48:06.634
‐ <i>He went in the ring
to announce he was retiring</i>

