01:07:45.144 --> 01:07:46.145
<i>a drug‐induced sleep‐‐</i>

1595
01:07:46.229 --> 01:07:48.064
with our son
climbing all over him

1596
01:07:48.189 --> 01:07:49.566
and saying. "Daddy's asleep."

1597
01:07:49.691 --> 01:07:51.484
‐ To me.
the biggest thing again

1598
01:07:51.568 --> 01:07:54.153
was Cameron saying.
"Daddy's tired."

1599
01:07:54.237 --> 01:07:56.281
<i>And it sort of dawning on me</i>

1600
01:07:56.364 --> 01:07:59.075
<i>that he was now being able
to recognize</i>

1601
01:07:59.200 --> 01:08:02.745
clearly my state of mind.

1602
01:08:02.829 --> 01:08:05.373
<i>I went into the bathroom
and closed the door.</i>

1603
01:08:05.456 --> 01:08:07.166
<i>Looking at yourself
in the mirror</i>

1604
01:08:07.250 --> 01:08:09.168
and. you know.

1605
01:08:09.252 --> 01:08:12.046
I sat there and cried
like a baby and wept.

1606
01:08:12.171 --> 01:08:15.008
you know.
realizing that you are failing.

1607
01:08:15.133 --> 01:08:17.260
you know.
a two‐year‐old little boy.

1608
01:08:17.343 --> 01:08:19.220
And all of those things

1609
01:08:19.345 --> 01:08:22.515
sort of came crashing down
that night.

1610
01:08:22.640 --> 01:08:26.060
and I just‐‐it's the first
time I ever feel

1611
01:08:26.144 --> 01:08:28.479
like such a frickin' failure.

1612
01:08:28.605 --> 01:08:30.106
And I think that that was
the last straw for him.

1613
01:08:30.189 --> 01:08:32.817
and when he woke up
the next morning.

1614
01:08:32.900 --> 01:08:35.945
he told me he was never
taking pills or drinking again.

1615
01:08:36.029 --> 01:08:37.989
and from that point.
he didn't.

1616
01:08:38.072 --> 01:08:39.991
<i>It was an instantaneous
letting go</i>

1617
01:08:40.074 --> 01:08:41.534
<i>of the drugs and alcohol.</i>

1618
01:08:41.659 --> 01:08:43.369
‐ <i>I just called him
up out of the clear blue.</i>

1619
01:08:43.494 --> 01:08:46.539
I just asked him when the last
time he talked to Paul.

1620
01:08:46.664 --> 01:08:51.711
and. um. he just avoided
that situation.

1621
01:08:51.836 --> 01:08:56.924
I just said. "Man. you're wrong.
you got to call him."

1622
01:08:57.008 --> 01:08:58.593
I called Hunter
and let him know.

1623
01:08:58.676 --> 01:09:02.680
you know. how sorry I was
and how out of line I was.

1624
01:09:02.805 --> 01:09:04.807
And I said.
"I hope you can forgive me."

1625
01:09:04.932 --> 01:09:07.143
I needed that from Hunter.

1626
01:09:07.226 --> 01:09:09.479
For me. it was easy.
like. I didn't‐‐

1627
01:09:09.562 --> 01:09:11.981
as long as it
wasn't drugs talking to me.

1628
01:09:12.065 --> 01:09:13.650
‐ It's good to see you.

1629
01:09:13.691 --> 01:09:14.651
[patting]

1630
01:09:14.776 --> 01:09:15.652
‐ Group hug.

1631
01:09:15.777 --> 01:09:18.279
‐ <i>Of course.
I do regret the pain</i>

1632
01:09:18.363 --> 01:09:20.281
<i>that it caused people
in my life.</i>

1633
01:09:20.365 --> 01:09:23.076
but there is a part of that
that I don't think

1634
01:09:23.201 --> 01:09:27.288
that Michael Shawn Hickenbottom
can get

1635
01:09:27.372 --> 01:09:29.582
to where he got creatively

1636
01:09:29.707 --> 01:09:34.671
without a little bit of that
reckless. risky mindset.

1637
01:09:34.796 --> 01:09:38.758
I wouldn't have
had the guts to do it.

1638
01:09:38.841 --> 01:09:41.219
‐ <i>It was our
first Christmas together.</i>

1639
01:09:41.344 --> 01:09:43.429
and I gave Shawn a Bible
and some other books.

1640
01:09:43.513 --> 01:09:45.348
and he began reading them.

1641
01:09:45.473 --> 01:09:48.976
‐ <i>I had never had anything
that I could grasp</i>

1642
01:09:49.060 --> 01:09:51.312
<i>that was bigger
than the wrestling business.</i>

1643
01:09:51.396 --> 01:09:55.566
That's just not enough to base.
I don't know. a life on.

1644
01:09:56.651 --> 01:09:59.153
‐ <i>I worked at Cornerstone
Church in San Antonio. Texas.</i>

1645
01:09:59.237 --> 01:10:02.031
All of a sudden
I heard a deep voice said.

1646
01:10:02.115 --> 01:10:04.450
"I want to come
to a Bible study."

1647
01:10:04.534 --> 01:10:06.577
And then I got up from my desk

1648
01:10:06.703 --> 01:10:08.830
and stuck my head out the door.

1649
01:10:08.913 --> 01:10:10.748
and I said.
"Well. you can come to mine."

1650
01:10:10.873 --> 01:10:12.917
<i>When he left.
everybody came out and said.</i>

1651
01:10:12.959 --> 01:10:14.585
<i>"Do you know who that was?"</i>

1652
01:10:14.669 --> 01:10:16.212
<i>I said. "No. I don't know
who that was. who was it?"</i>

1653
01:10:16.337 --> 01:10:17.630
And they said.
"Shawn Michaels."

1654
01:10:17.714 --> 01:10:19.674
and I said.
"Well. who's Shawn Michaels?"

1655
01:10:22.093 --> 01:10:23.553
<i>He said. "Well. first. Keith.</i>

1656
01:10:23.678 --> 01:10:26.305
<i>I want you to pray
for my back."</i>

1657
01:10:26.389 --> 01:10:28.057
He says.
"I've been out of wrestling

1658
01:10:28.182 --> 01:10:29.308
<i>and I want to go back."</i>

1659
01:10:29.392 --> 01:10:31.060
<i>I said. "Well.
there's a simple prayer</i>

1660
01:10:31.144 --> 01:10:32.478
<i>that we can pray together."</i>

1661
01:10:32.603 --> 01:10:34.981
<i>And while he was saying
that prayer.</i>

1662
01:10:35.064 --> 01:10:38.359
tears just come
out of his eyes.

1663
01:10:38.484 --> 01:10:40.486
‐ <i>I got nobody
to blame but me.</i>

1664
01:10:40.570 --> 01:10:43.489
<i>and I don't have anything
in common with the other dude.</i>

1665
01:10:43.573 --> 01:10:45.408
<i>and I don't know
how I got that way.</i>

1666
01:10:45.533 --> 01:10:48.244
It wasn't from family.
It wasn't from upbringing.

1667
01:10:48.327 --> 01:10:50.079
‐ He was so desperate

1668
01:10:50.163 --> 01:10:54.208
to get back in that close
relationship with Rebecca

1669
01:10:54.333 --> 01:10:55.918
<i>and his son.</i>

1670
01:10:56.002 --> 01:10:57.795
‐ <i>I was now a dad.
I was a husband.</i>

1671
01:10:57.837 --> 01:11:03.134
and I was really devoted
and thrilled about that.

1672
01:11:03.259 --> 01:11:04.469
‐ You're like a child.

1673
01:11:04.594 --> 01:11:07.346
you just want to tell
everybody. "I've been saved."

1674
01:11:14.312 --> 01:11:15.980
<i>‐ Once Shawn got
his life together</i>

1675
01:11:16.022 --> 01:11:18.232
<i>and found Christ.
it was night and day.</i>

1676
01:11:18.316 --> 01:11:19.692
<i>When he looks back
at his life.</i>

1677
01:11:19.776 --> 01:11:22.153
that's the biggest thing
that he ever did.

1678
01:11:22.236 --> 01:11:23.529
‐ <i>You were
dealing with the grownup</i>

1679
01:11:23.654 --> 01:11:24.906
<i>when Shawn came back.</i>

1680
01:11:25.031 --> 01:11:27.825
<i>someone who was there
to do business.</i>

1681
01:11:27.909 --> 01:11:31.162
Shawn was a lot calmer
and much easier to deal with.

1682
01:11:31.245 --> 01:11:32.830
‐ <i>Shawn Michaels of old</i>

1683
01:11:32.955 --> 01:11:34.582
<i>is very different from Shawn
Hickenbottom.</i>

1684
01:11:34.707 --> 01:11:35.917
<i>the man I married.</i>

1685
01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:37.960
<i>The sexy boy
and all that kinda stuff.</i>

1686
01:11:38.002 --> 01:11:39.253
and his cocky attitude

1687
01:11:39.337 --> 01:11:41.130
and the cocky little smile
that he does.

1688
01:11:41.214 --> 01:11:45.301
That's so far
from who he really is.

1689
01:11:45.426 --> 01:11:47.011
‐ <i>I remember
somebody asking me.</i>

1690
01:11:47.136 --> 01:11:50.556
<i>they said. you know. "Hey.
I heard Shawn found religion."</i>

1691
01:11:50.640 --> 01:11:52.058
<i>Yeah. They laughed.</i>

1692
01:11:52.141 --> 01:11:56.979
and I said. "I don't anybody
that died OD'ing on religion."

1693
01:11:57.104 --> 01:11:58.648
‐ <i>He had called Triple H.</i>

1694
01:11:58.731 --> 01:12:01.818
<i>He thanked Hunter
for the time on the road</i>

1695
01:12:01.901 --> 01:12:04.695
because before his marriage
to me.

1696
01:12:04.821 --> 01:12:08.449
the one who took
care of him was Hunter.

1697
01:12:08.533 --> 01:12:10.993
That night. after Shawn
had gone to bed.

1698
01:12:11.077 --> 01:12:14.747
he woke up in the morning and
the pain was gone in his back.

1699
01:12:14.872 --> 01:12:16.749
<i>It was definitely a miracle.</i>

1700
01:12:16.833 --> 01:12:19.710
<i>So. he was physically ready
to go back in the ring.</i>

1701
01:12:19.836 --> 01:12:24.048
and I knew that the Lord
would take care of him.

1702
01:12:24.173 --> 01:12:25.716
‐ <i>We were kind of
having conversations</i>

1703
01:12:25.800 --> 01:12:27.718
<i>at the time. and then he said.</i>

1704
01:12:27.844 --> 01:12:29.262
"I want my son to see me
do this one time."

1705
01:12:29.345 --> 01:12:30.805
he said. "But I don't know
that I can do it.

1706
01:12:30.888 --> 01:12:32.723
I don't know physically
if I can or not."

1707
01:12:32.807 --> 01:12:34.308
and he said. "If I'm going to.

1708
01:12:34.392 --> 01:12:37.436
I only trust one person.
that's you.

1709
01:12:37.520 --> 01:12:40.481
If you consider it.
I would love to do it.

1710
01:12:40.565 --> 01:12:44.402
What do you think?"

1711
01:12:44.527 --> 01:12:48.030
‐ <i>Moments away
from the non‐sanctioned fight</i>

1712
01:12:48.155 --> 01:12:51.659
between two men who were.
at one time. best friends.

1713
01:12:51.701 --> 01:12:53.786
Shawn Michaels and Triple H.

1714
01:12:53.870 --> 01:12:59.375
<i>Shawn Michaels last wrestled
1.609 days ago.</i>

1715
01:12:59.500 --> 01:13:02.044
<i>if you can believe that.</i>

1716
01:13:02.169 --> 01:13:03.337
‐ <i>His whole family was there.</i>

1717
01:13:03.421 --> 01:13:06.048
<i>You know.
they were all scared to death.</i>

1718
01:13:06.173 --> 01:13:07.842
Got in the ring.
did a couple of things.

1719
01:13:07.967 --> 01:13:09.635
[bell rings]

1720
01:13:09.719 --> 01:13:12.722
<i>Never missed a beat.
not a moment. not an anything.</i>

1721
01:13:12.847 --> 01:13:14.724
‐ I was on my chair
like a redneck.

1722
01:13:14.807 --> 01:13:16.517
just screaming
and yelling for him.

1723
01:13:16.601 --> 01:13:17.894
<i>Of course. I cried at the end.</i>

1724
01:13:17.977 --> 01:13:19.478
‐ <i>Like.
how is this possible.</i>

1725
01:13:19.604 --> 01:13:24.525
<i>that he is this good still.
after all that time</i>

1726
01:13:24.609 --> 01:13:28.821
and injury and everything else?
Unbelievable.

1727
01:13:28.905 --> 01:13:32.783
‐ <i>It was just as easy
as the day is long.</i>

1728
01:13:32.867 --> 01:13:34.660
it was poetic.
it was phenomenal.

1729
01:13:34.744 --> 01:13:38.205
it was everything that is right
and good about the world

1730
01:13:38.289 --> 01:13:41.334
in this line of work. and.
you know. my family there.

1731
01:13:41.417 --> 01:13:42.960
<i>out there
with my best friend.</i>

1732
01:13:43.085 --> 01:13:50.134
‐ <i>The Heartbreak Kid.
Shawn Michaels!</i>

1733
01:13:50.217 --> 01:13:51.802
‐ <i>After the Summerslam.</i>

1734
01:13:51.886 --> 01:13:54.221
<i>that's when there was
a sense of peace and joy</i>

1735
01:13:54.347 --> 01:13:56.807
<i>in the midst of doing
your job and your family.</i>

1736
01:13:56.933 --> 01:14:01.270
combining these two worlds
that I've never had together.

1737
01:14:01.354 --> 01:14:02.939
and I'm not even
the same person.

1738
01:14:03.022 --> 01:14:06.525
And now.
and it all feels so right.

1739
01:14:06.609 --> 01:14:07.735
That's as good as it gets.
you know.

1740
01:14:07.818 --> 01:14:10.488
it's heaven on Earth here
in this room.

1741
01:14:10.571 --> 01:14:12.990
‐ Shawn Michaels
changed completely

1742
01:14:13.115 --> 01:14:14.367
as a human being.

1743
01:14:14.492 --> 01:14:16.243
<i>And somehow. as a character.</i>

1744
01:14:16.369 --> 01:14:21.874
<i>he managed to keep a lot
of the aura that he always had.</i>

1745
01:14:21.999 --> 01:14:26.587
I could argue that Shawn was
at his best after he came back.

1746
01:14:26.671 --> 01:14:29.757
[cheers and applause]

1747
01:14:29.840 --> 01:14:31.634
‐ <i>To me.</i>

1748
01:14:31.717 --> 01:14:36.222
the greatest in‐ring performer

1749
01:14:36.347 --> 01:14:38.307
of all time.

1750
01:14:39.642 --> 01:14:41.560
<i>[soft music]</i>

1751
01:14:41.644 --> 01:14:43.729
‐ It gets more difficult

1752
01:14:43.854 --> 01:14:46.023
to find a new mountain.
a new challenge.

1753
01:14:46.148 --> 01:14:48.651
Sometimes that mountain
or that new challenge

1754
01:14:48.693 --> 01:14:49.860
just isn't there.

1755
01:14:49.944 --> 01:14:51.404
And so later on in my career.
I learned that

1756
01:14:51.529 --> 01:14:54.281
when I disconnect from it.
something will usually happen.

1757
01:14:54.365 --> 01:14:56.158
and. you know.
the one with Flair

1758
01:14:56.200 --> 01:14:59.328
is the one I honestly
always speak of.

1759
01:14:59.453 --> 01:15:01.914
Remember the story
of Old Yeller?

1760
01:15:01.998 --> 01:15:05.126
The Showstopper's gonna
take you. Old Yeller.

1761
01:15:05.209 --> 01:15:10.339
behind the woodshed
and put you out of your misery.

1762
01:15:10.464 --> 01:15:14.510
I lost myself in that drama.
[laughs]

1763
01:15:14.635 --> 01:15:16.012
<i>I get a call from my buddy.
Kenny.</i>

1764
01:15:16.137 --> 01:15:17.888
<i>who's now been
made aware of the match.</i>

1765
01:15:18.014 --> 01:15:19.890
It's like. oh my goodness.
he said. "Can you believe it?"

1766
01:15:20.016 --> 01:15:23.811
‐ It was overwhelming to think
that the guy that we idolized

1767
01:15:23.853 --> 01:15:27.606
that we would watch a little TV
box in San Antonio. Texas.

1768
01:15:27.690 --> 01:15:30.276
somehow their lives were going
to interconnect.

1769
01:15:30.359 --> 01:15:33.195
Ric was his guy.
He absolutely loved Ric Flair.

1770
01:15:33.279 --> 01:15:36.365
‐ <i>Kenny took me back
to that time.</i>

1771
01:15:39.744 --> 01:15:43.247
<i>‐ This was why I went
from New York to Orlando.</i>

1772
01:15:43.372 --> 01:15:46.167
was to see this moment.

1773
01:15:46.208 --> 01:15:47.209
[bell rings]

1774
01:15:47.293 --> 01:15:48.753
‐ <i>Now in this match.</i>

1775
01:15:48.836 --> 01:15:53.382
<i>should Ric Flair lose.
he must retire.</i>

1776
01:15:53.466 --> 01:15:54.759
‐ <i>I remember feeling</i>

1777
01:15:54.842 --> 01:15:56.802
like the way Ric Flair
started this match.

1778
01:15:56.927 --> 01:15:59.805
that he had a chance.

1779
01:15:59.930 --> 01:16:02.224
[grunts]

1780
01:16:02.308 --> 01:16:04.977
‐ There's no other way
to put it‐‐he carried me.

1781
01:16:05.061 --> 01:16:08.564
He gave everything
that anybody could ever give

1782
01:16:08.689 --> 01:16:10.232
to a match that night.

1783
01:16:10.316 --> 01:16:13.194
‐ <i>Oh. wait a minute.
wait a minute. look out.</i>

1784
01:16:13.319 --> 01:16:15.613
<i>Good grief!</i>

1785
01:16:15.696 --> 01:16:17.573
<i>Oh. not again!</i>

1786
01:16:17.656 --> 01:16:18.866
‐ <i>It becomes clear</i>

1787
01:16:18.991 --> 01:16:22.244
that Ric Flair
just doesn't have enough.

1788
01:16:22.328 --> 01:16:25.247
<i>I love this part. I could
tear up talking about it.</i>

1789
01:16:25.372 --> 01:16:28.292
<i>Flair. like an old dog.
still fighting.</i>

1790
01:16:28.375 --> 01:16:30.127
he thinks he still has it.

1791
01:16:30.211 --> 01:16:34.131
And that's when Shawn sort
of has to have that moment

1792
01:16:34.256 --> 01:16:36.634
where he says.
"I'm sorry. I love you."

1793
01:16:36.759 --> 01:16:38.761
‐ <i>Flair wants to fight.</i>

1794
01:16:38.844 --> 01:16:40.971
‐ <i>And just turns
the lights out.</i>

1795
01:16:41.055 --> 01:16:46.477
It was as beautiful and perfect
an ending to a wrestling match

1796
01:16:46.602 --> 01:16:48.479
as you will ever have.

1797
01:16:48.521 --> 01:16:50.898
<i>‐ He knew I didn't
want to go.</i>

1798
01:16:51.023 --> 01:16:53.734
<i>and he said.
"I love you."</i>

1799
01:16:53.818 --> 01:16:54.902
<i>It's a great moment
in wrestling.</i>

1800
01:16:54.985 --> 01:16:56.737
<i>I don't care what anyone says.</i>

1801
01:16:56.821 --> 01:16:59.782
you can't replace something
like that.

1802
01:16:59.865 --> 01:17:01.158
‐ <i>Unashamed</i>

1803
01:17:01.242 --> 01:17:03.619
<i>that it was my love letter to.
you know.</i>

1804
01:17:03.702 --> 01:17:07.706
the wrestling business
and to Ric Flair.

1805
01:17:12.336 --> 01:17:16.173
‐ It is show day.
and we're off to the shi‐zow.

1806
01:17:16.257 --> 01:17:19.760
<i>I've been doing this
for 35 years.</i>

1807
01:17:19.844 --> 01:17:20.970
and days like today.

1808
01:17:21.053 --> 01:17:22.930
it's a different kind
of anxiety that I have now.

1809
01:17:23.013 --> 01:17:24.765
I have anxiety
for the performers

1810
01:17:24.849 --> 01:17:26.892
for the entire show as a whole.

1811
01:17:27.017 --> 01:17:29.186
For me it's just
all fantastic.

1812
01:17:29.311 --> 01:17:31.522
especially when it goes well
for them.

1813
01:17:31.647 --> 01:17:33.023
and they come back
and they're jacked.

1814
01:17:33.107 --> 01:17:34.900
It's ten times better than‐‐

1815
01:17:35.025 --> 01:17:36.652
than when I had
that opportunity.

1816
01:17:36.777 --> 01:17:38.696
This is where
I'm supposed to be.

1817
01:17:38.821 --> 01:17:41.740
I absolutely love it.

1818
01:17:43.367 --> 01:17:45.536
<i>[soft music]</i>

1819
01:17:45.619 --> 01:17:46.871
‐ What moment would you say

1820
